   PLOT (Eng):
   Document name: Digging for the truth: God's Gold (Episode 1/2)

   Hosted by adventurer Hunter Ellis (Tactical to Practical). Hunter tracks the
   priceless golden relics taken from Jerusalem's Second Temple in AD 70.
   Adventure has a new name! Host, explorer and survival expert Hunter Ellis
   takes a fresh look at the world's greatest ancient mysteries and puts
   adventure back into history as he travels to some of the most intriguing,
   remote and physically challenging locations in the world. With a fresh and
   engaging approach to archaeology, Hunter goes to extremes and takes us along
   for the ride.
   Looted from the Second Temple by the Romans, golden artifacts including a
   seven-branched candelabrum have slipped in and out of history and legend for
   2000 years. Treasures of unparalleled importance, some say that if the lamp
   were auctioned bids would open at one billion dollars. But it's knowledge,
   not riches, that drives Hunter Ellis around the world to track these glorious
   relics.
   In the second installment of this thrilling two-part DIGGING FOR THE TRUTH,
   Hunter discovers clues that lead him to the final resting place of the Temple
   treasures. In tracking the artifacts, he uncovers the complicated and
   fascinating history of Judeo-Christian tradition and of the tides of
   civilizations over the past two millennia.
   GOD'S GOLD may lead Hunter back to Israel, but his real journey is back
   in time.
